      <link>https://tilmanbauer.github.io/teaching/2016-2017/algebraic_topology/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 31 Oct 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://tilmanbauer.github.io/teaching/2016-2017/algebraic_topology/</guid>
      <description>This PhD level course continues where the advanced level course SF2735/MM8020 Homological Algebra and Algebraic Topology left off. It covers homotopy theory and CW-complexes, cohomology operations, gives an introduction to stable homotopy theory, and then proceeds with either bordism theory or K-theory, depending on the participants&amp;rsquo; preferences. The intended audience of this course is PhD students of all areas of mathematics.</description>
